Constable Amanda Ladlokova was shot dead in the attack on Tuesday night, while her colleague was critically wounded. CAPE TOWN - A suspected gunman in an attack on two police officers will remain behind bars until his next court appearance next week.Ashwin Kennedy, 19, faces charges of murder and attempted murder after he allegedly ambushed two officers for their firearms.Constable Amanda Ladlokova was shot dead in the attack on Tuesday night, while her colleague was critically wounded.The court has heard the sergeant survived by playing dead.Police believe the teenage suspect did not act alone, adding his two accomplices are still at large.It's alleged three men ambushed the two officers while they were responding to a complaint of domestic violence on Tuesday night.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)